Ultratech

Target IP: 10.10.226.105

Scanning



There are four TCP ports open on the target machine: two HTTP, one FTP, and one SSH. I will start the enumeration with the two HTTP applications.

Enumeration

Port 8081: HTTP Node.js Express Framework

The application on this port looks like some sort o REST API.

Port 31331: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed when we browse to this port on a web-browser. Searching for source-code does not provide helpful information.


Doing a directory search leads to helpful information, with one being robots.txt. The robots.txtcontains an entry called /utech_sitemap.txt.


And this entry contains three directories shown above.


The /partners.html is an interesting page because it allows us to login. I had no login details, so I decided to do more enumeration.



The /js directory is interesting as it contains three JavaScript files. The first file is the most interesting as it contains the code for the REST API running on port 8081.The URL path string gives away another hidden directory /ping at port 8081.


There is an interesting parameter called ip. Maybe we can perform command injections using this parameter?


And it worked. By using %0a, I am able to append more commands so the server can execute it. This is easy bypassing. From the picture above, there is an interesting file called utech.db.sqlite. I will try to read it using the payload %0acat%20utech.db.sqlite.


And we get the contents of the database above! There are two users: r00t and admin.


Using the website hashes, I obtained the password of their users. Maybe we can spray these credentials against FTP and SSH.
r00t:n100906
Madmin:mrsheafy


I was able to spray the credentials of r00t to gain access to the application on port 8081 /partners.html page.

Exploitation


Using r00t:n100906, I gained a foothold on the machine.

Privilege Escalation


Gaining a root shell by breaking out of the docker group.

Flags


The challenge of this task is to read the id_rsa key of the root user. And this challenge is complete.
